A-Eng. SB 1571
1 that is likely to be used for human consumption by any means, including in the forms of
2 bidis, cigars, cheroots, stogies, periques, granulated, plug cut, crimp cut, ready rubbed and other
3 smoking tobacco, snuff, snuff flour, cavendish, plug and twist tobacco, fine-cut and other chewing
4 tobaccos, shorts, refuse scraps, clippings, cuttings and sweepings of tobacco and other forms of
5 tobacco[, prepared in a manner that makes the tobacco suitable for chewing or smoking in a pipe or
6 otherwise, or for both chewing and smoking], oral nicotine pouches, nicotine lozenges and other
7 products that contain nicotine;
8 [(B)] (ii) Cigarettes as defined in ORS 323.010 (1); or
9 [(C)] (iii) A device that:
10 [(i)] (I) Can be used to deliver tobacco products to a person using the device; and
11 [(ii)] (II) Has not been approved by the United States Food and Drug Administration for sale
12 as a tobacco cessation product or for any other therapeutic purpose, if the product is marketed and
13 sold solely for the approved purpose.
14 (B) “Tobacco products” does not include an article that is food, as defined in ORS 616.205,
15 if the article does not contain nicotine or contains no more than trace amounts of naturally
16 occurring nicotine.
17 (2) It is unlawful to:
18 (a) [To] Violate ORS 167.755.
19 (b) [To] Fail as a retailer of tobacco products to post a notice substantially similar to the notice
20 described in subsection (3) of this section in a location that is clearly visible to the seller and the
21 purchaser of the tobacco products.
22 (c) [To] Fail as a retailer of inhalant delivery systems to post a notice in a location that is
23 clearly visible to the seller and the purchaser of the inhalant delivery systems that it is unlawful
24 to sell inhalant delivery systems to persons under 21 years of age. The Oregon Health Authority
25 shall adopt by rule the content of the notice required under this paragraph.
26 (d) [To] Distribute, sell or allow to be sold an inhalant delivery system if the inhalant delivery
27 system is not labeled in accordance with rules adopted by the authority.
28 (e) [To] Distribute, sell or allow to be sold an inhalant delivery system if the inhalant delivery
29 system is not packaged in child-resistant safety packaging, as required by the authority by rule.
30 (f) [To] Distribute, sell or allow to be sold an inhalant delivery system if the inhalant delivery
31 system is packaged in a manner that is attractive to minors, as determined by the authority by rule.
32 (g) [To] Distribute, sell or allow to be sold cigarettes in any form other than a sealed package
33 that contains at least 20 cigarettes.
34 (3) The notice required by subsection (2)(b) of this section must be substantially as follows:
35 _______________________________________________________________________________________
36
37 NOTICE
38 The sale of tobacco in any form to persons under 21 years of age is prohibited by law. Any
39 person who sells, or allows to be sold, tobacco to a person under 21 years of age is in violation of
40 Oregon law.
41 _______________________________________________________________________________________
42
43 (4) Rules adopted under subsection (2)(d), (e) and (f) of this section must be consistent with any
44 regulation adopted by the United States Food and Drug Administration related to labeling or pack-
45 aging requirements for inhalant delivery systems.
